Reckless Truck driver causes multiple collision. According to JMPD spokesman Wayne Minaar the accident happened on Saturday behind flora clinic on the down hill of William Nicol Street. Minnaar said the truck that caused an accident was transporting chrome from Rustenburg to City Deep. "The truck collided into rear of van and SUV vehicle which were both stationary at a traffic light .The driver of the van was seriously injured and was airlifted to Milpark Hospital," he said. He added that the passenger of the van was also serious and was transported to Flora clinic . Minnaar said the driver of the SUV was only slightly injured. " The truck driver was arrested and charged at Florida Police Station for reckless and negligent driving and for transporting chrome without a permit. William Nicol Street in Florida has a very steep decline , and there are signs which prohibit trucks of 5ton and above to use that road," said Minnaar.  He explained that recently there has been complaints received from the Florida Blockwatch , that big trucks were disregarding those signs . " JMPD officers have issued dozens of fines of R500 each to drivers of big trucks who disregarded the signs."  Minaar said William Nicol Street had to be closed for more than three hours for the chrome to be removed and for the accident scene to be cleared.